## Before vs After: goals.vue

````carousel
### Before (❌ MVVM violation — View calling API directly)
```typescript
// goals.vue — had 260+ lines of business logic in the page
const fetchGoals = async () => {
  const data = await useApi()(`/sme/goals?smeId=${currentSmeId.value}`) // ← direct API in View!
  goals.value = data
  updateFilterCounts()
}
const handleCreateGoal = async (goalData) => {
  await useApi()('/sme/goals', { method: 'POST', body: { ...goalData } })
}
// ... 200 more lines ...
```
<!-- slide -->
### After (✅ Clean View — pure UI binding)
```typescript
// goals.vue — 35 lines, delegates everything to the composable
const {
  goals, filteredGoals, loading, selectedGoal, avgProgress, radarData,
  activeFilter, activeCreatorFilter, statusFilterTabs, creatorFilterOptions,
  showCreateGoalModal, showProofModal, goalIdToComplete,
  fetchGoals, createGoal, pauseGoal, deleteGoal, markAsAchieved, openProofModal,
} = useGoals()

onMounted(() => fetchGoals())
```
````

---

## Before vs After: Admin Store

| Before | After |
|---|---|
| 1 file, **1,542 lines** | 4 focused stores + 1 index barrel |
| Mixed: users + programs + framework + logs | Each store owns exactly one domain |
| Hard to test, easy to cause regressions | Each store is independently testable |

**Import going forward:**
```typescript
// Preferred — import only what you need
import { useAdminUsersStore }    from '~/stores/admin/admin.users.store'
import { useAdminProgramsStore } from '~/stores/admin/admin.programs.store'
import { useAdminFrameworkStore } from '~/stores/admin/admin.framework.store'
import { useAdminReportsStore }  from '~/stores/admin/admin.reports.store'

// Or use the barrel
import { useAdminUsersStore } from '~/stores/admin'
```

> [!NOTE]
> The original [admin.store.ts](file:///Users/paypanha/SMEFrontend/stores/admin.store.ts) is **untouched** — any existing page that imports `useAdminStore` will still work during migration. You can update pages gradually.

